.TH MILLENNIUM\-DIAG 1 "July 9, 2026" "millennium-helpers" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
millennium-diag \- diagnose Millennium and Steam helper health
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B millennium-diag
[\fICOMMAND\fR] [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Runs a read-only diagnostics report by default. Can also show logs, upload a
redacted report, or run doctor mode to auto-repair common problems.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B (none)
Print the diagnostics report (default).
.TP
.B doctor
Detect and repair partial or broken installations.
.TP
.B logs
Display recent Millennium and Steam WebHelper startup logs.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-f ", " \-\-fix
Alias for the
.B doctor
command.
.TP
.B \-\-force
Force doctor repairs even if the system looks healthy.
.TP
.B \-\-json
Emit the diagnostics report as structured JSON.
.TP
.BR \-l ", " \-\-follow
Follow (tail \-f) real-time log output with
.BR logs .
.TP
.BR \-d ", " \-\-dry\-run
Simulate doctor repairs without modifying anything.
.TP
.BR \-s ", " \-\-share
Upload a redacted diagnostic report to a pastebin and print a short link.
.TP
.BR \-V ", " \-\-version
Show version information.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show help message.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR millennium-repair (1),
.BR millennium-upgrade (1),
.BR millennium-schedule (1)
